{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5698: props default value inconsistent behavior with vue 2",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:29.048959+00:00",
  "text": "props default value inconsistent behavior with vue 2\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.31\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[stackblitz.com](https://stackblitz.com/edit/vue-erg87v?file=src%2FApp.vue)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nVue 3: https://stackblitz.com/edit/vue-erg87v?file=src%2FApp.vue\r\n\r\nVue 2: https://stackblitz.com/edit/vue2-vue-cli-mjakzv?file=src%2FApp.vue\r\n\r\n\r\nIn Vue 3:\r\n1. input `obj.name`, type 123  (obj.name: [] doesn't update )\r\n2. click first input, type anything to trigger child component update  (obj.name update to obj.name: [123])\r\n3. input `str1`,  error: `proxy set handler returned false for property '\"str1\"'`\r\n\r\nIn Vue 2:\r\n1. input `obj.name`, type 123  (obj.name: [] update to  obj.name: [123])\r\n2. click first input, type anything to trigger child component update  (obj.name: [123] doesn't update)\r\n3. input `str1`,  warning: `[Vue warn]: Avoid mutating a prop directly since the value will be overwritten whenever the parent component re-renders. Instead, use a data or computed property based on the prop's value. Prop being mutated: \"str1\"\r\n`\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nVue 2 behavior is more  reasonable\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nabove\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
